HEADWORD: Phoronis
<hw>Pho*ro"nis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>Phoronis</ets>, a surname of Io, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A remarkable genus of marine worms having tentacles around the
mouth. It is usually classed with the gephyreans. Its larva
(<it>Actinotrocha</it>) undergoes a peculiar metamorphosis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

